    "en": "Herbal preparation derived from Job&#039;s Tears. Yiyiren is a grain, also known as Job's Tears, that is native to Southeast Asia. Used both as a food and medicine, it has sweet, cooling properties and affects the lung, spleen and stomach meridians. ..."
